            "answer_text": "Nagari and Devanagari are the names given to the scripts used by the merchant community of south India who traded throughout India. When shifted the writing material from palm leaf to cloth and silk they ought to change the ordinary writers and appoint artists who used brush and coloured inks. Instead of straight lines they drew curved lines. This resulted the nagari script. Tamil merchants are the originaters and probagators of nagari script ",
